In the latest Discovering.... documentary where top music journalists discuss Radiohead's rise from Oxfordshire school friends to rock superstars.
Signed by EMI and their first album Pablo Honey eventually became a hit after its biggest single Creep was regularly featured on MTV. Here, we find out how their album The Bends was the beginning of their chart success.
